<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
The two Chilean species differ macroscopically, 
<taxonomicName authority="P.R.Johnst., 2021" authorityName="P.R.Johnst." authorityYear="2021" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Nothofagaceae" genus="Brahmaculus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Brahmaculus osornoensis" order="Helotiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="osornoensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Brahmaculus osornoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
having noticeably broader stipes than 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. magellanicus" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" rank="species" species="magellanicus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">B. magellanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and slightly longer ascospores. 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. osornoensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" rank="species" species="osornoensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">B. osornoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from 
<taxonomicName class="Leotiomycetes" family="Clavicipitaceae" genus="Nothofagus" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Nothofagus dombeyi" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="dombeyi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Nothofagus dombeyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
forest in northern Patagonia on Volcan Osorno in the Vicente Perez 
<taxonomicName class="Leotiomycetes" family="Clavicipitaceae" genus="Nothofagus" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="order">Rosales</taxonomicName>
National Park. It is possible that this 
<taxonomicName authority="P.R.Johnst., 2021" authorityName="P.R.Johnst." authorityYear="2021" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Nothofagaceae" genus="Brahmaculus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Brahmaculus" order="Helotiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Brahmaculus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species is restricted to the wetter and warmer forests in northern Patagonia, but more specimens are needed to determine the range of the species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
